---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <section
        class="flex flex-col relative min-h-screen m-4 mt-16 gap-8 items-center p-4"
    >
        <h1 class="pt-24 text-5xl text-vyoma-blue">Dwadash  Jyotirlinga Temples Tour</h1>

        <div
            class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-left max-w-screen-lg w-full text-white"
        >
            <div class="flex flex-col">
                <p class="text-lg">
                    Jyotirlinga is considered as one of the prime worship spots for the devoters of Lord Shiva. It is believed in Hinduism that jyotirlinga is the resplendent flame of the almighty solidified to make the worship of it simple. It is said that there are 64 jyotirlingas in India. However, 12 jyotirlingas are presumed to be very auspicious and revered among them. These jyotirlingas are positioned in eight states i.e. Gujarat, Maharashtra, Tamilnadu, Andhra Pradesh, Madhya Pradesh, Jharkhand, Uttarakhand and Uttar Pradesh. As per the Hindu mythologies, visiting jyotirlingas is a pilgrimage that wades off all the sins and makes the soul sacrosanct and pure. The devotees visiting these jyotirlingas become, chaste, pure and calm. They turn illuminated and enlightened with highest and divine knowledge. According to the Hindu folklores, one who visits these holy sites attains all the Siddhis and powers. This 23 nights and 24 days itinerary takes the tourists to all the 12 jyotirlingas positioned from east to west in India. This tour is perfect for all those who want to relax their minds and get drenched in utter spirituality.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col">
                <h3 class="text-vyoma-blue text-2xl">Itinerary</h3>
                <div class="text-lg">
                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            1
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 1: Mumbai - Rajkot</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>Arrival Transfer Sightseeing tour Lunch Dinner</p>
                    <p>Other Benefits (On Arrival): Breakfast, Transfers, Stay Included</p>
                    <p>On arrival in Mumbai, meet our representative who will transfer you to the railway station to catch the train to Rajkot. An overnight train journey.</p>

                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            2
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 2: Rajkot - Dwarka</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>On arrival at Rajkot in the morning, our representative will transfer you to the hotel in Rajkot where you can enjoy the breakfast and get freshen up. Later, get transferred to your pre-booked hotel in Dwarka. It will take about 5 hours to reach Dwarka. In the evening, leave for a visit to Dwarkadhish Ji and Nageshwar Temple. Later return back to your hotel in Dwarka for an overnight stay.</p>

                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            3
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 3: Dwarka - Somnath</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>In the morning after breakfast, we will leave for Somnath by road. On arrival at Somnath, check in at the hotel. After lunch in the hotel, we will proceed to visit Veraval. In the evening, offer prayers in Somnath Temple. Enjoy an overnight stay in the hotel.</p>

                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            4
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 4: Somnath - Ujjain</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>Today after Abhishek Puja in the morning, enjoy the delicious breakfast. Thereafter, get transferred to the railway station to take the train to Ujjain. An overnight train journey.</p>

                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            5
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 5: Ujjain - Omkareshwar - Ujjain</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>On reaching Ujjain, meet our tour representative to get the assisted transfer to the hotel. Check in at the hotel and get relaxed. Afterwards, we will drive to Omkareshwar, which is located on an island and houses fourth jyotirlinga. In the evening, we will drive back to Ujjain for an overnight stay in the hotel.</p>

                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            6
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 6: Ujjain - Haridwar</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>In the morning, attend the Puja in Mahakaleshwar Ji and proceed to Bhairav Baba and Ma Shaktipeeth. After having lunch, leave for railway station to catch the train to Haridwar. An overnight train journey.</p>

                    <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                        <div
                            class="flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-vyoma-blue text-white text-lg font-bold"
                        >
                            7
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-vyoma-blue">Day 7: Haridwar</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p>On arrival at Haridwar, check in at your pre-booked hotel. In the evening, attend the Ganga Arti. Later, return back to the hotel for dinner and an overnight stay.</p>

                    <!-- Additional days itinerary can be added here following the same structure -->
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
